<h1>jQuery Matrix Features</h1>
<p>The usage column is controlled by the horizontal checkboxes along the top.</p>
<p>The alphabet contains access keys to their corresponding letter, so if you Select All, you can then press the access key (or click the letter) to move to that section of the table. Access keys are spotting in their browser support however.</p>
<p>Click the funnel to hide/show  filters.</p>
<p>The Category filter corresponds to the categories down the left-side of the <a href="http://api.jquery.com/">jQuery API</a> page. The <a href="http://api.jquery.com/browser/">dynamic API browser</a> is interesting.</p>
<p>The Attribute filter needs some explaining:</p>
<ul>
	<li>A &quot;<a href="../Matrix/jQuery.cfm?Attr=getter&Usage=All">getter</a>&quot; is a method that returns a value, and doesn't change anything.</li>
	<li>A &quot;<a href="../Matrix/jQuery.cfm?Attr=setter&Usage=All">setter</a>&quot; is a method that sets a value.</li>
	<li>A &quot;<a href="../Matrix/jQuery.cfm?Attr=trigger&Usage=All">trigger</a>&quot; is a method that fires an event. If you want to fire the click event yourself for instance.</li>
	<li>A &quot;<a href="../Matrix/jQuery.cfm?Attr=register&Usage=All">register</a>&quot; is the method that is fired.</li>
	<li>A &quot;<a href="../Matrix/jQuery.cfm?Attr=property&Usage=All">property</a>&quot; is a single value, or a set of name/value pairs.</li>
	<li>A &quot;<a href="../Matrix/jQuery.cfm?Attr=setting&Usage=All">setting</a>&quot; is a parameter passed into a method. </li>
</ul>
<p>The returns column comes from the jQuery documentation. A getter will return a different type of variable than a setter. For example, the attr getter returns a string, whereas the attr setter returns a jQuery object.</p>
